Great movie, ending could have been better

I cannot for the life of me understand the hate towards this movie. I absolutely loved it and thought it was the best of the current trilogy, edging out the first movie The Force Awakens. I grew up with A New Hope so there is a lot of nostalgia for me and the original trilogy, but this movie had all of the "feels" and action you could want in a movie like Star Wars. Were there things that could have brought more clarity, story lines that could have been tied up better, sure, but that is most films. It just seems like everyone wants to bash movies for what they "aren't" instead of enjoy them for what they "are"! Rant over.
What was Fin going to tell Rey?  Pretty bow.  Well done JJ!
Great job! I've been a fan since I was 6 years old and I think this movie was very well done.

The movie was amazing, I love the little moments in it pulling from previous shows, I also loved how they portray palpaltine along with bringing force ability's that have been unseen from the movies and which came from the games.

The movie ruins the original trilogy and is an insult to star wars fans all around the globe. There are very few good parts but for the most part, it's pretty pad. 
It's a total mess. This trilogy has no clear line it follows. You'd be hard pressed to find any coloration between this and the last two movies. I'm not going put spoilers in, but a certain character feels rushed, like he was put in last minute, to bait people... I'm very disappointed in this movie and more so in this trilogy, which is wasted potential.
Despite the messy trilogy, Abrams salvages what little he could and brought the films to a fan devoted ending.
too many cooks in the Disney Era Star Wars films.  At times, it just feels like someone said BIGGER, make it BIGGER.

If you're able to turn your brain off and just enjoy the visuals and sound, it's a somewhat entertaining movie.

If you CAN'T turn your brain off, prepare to get mentally annihilated by the number of contrivances, plot holes, dead ends, inconsistencies, endless McGuffins, cheap 1-liners, etc etc.
